---
alwaysApply: true
---

Only change files necessary for the current step.

Never invent APIs. If unsure, search the codebase for examples first.

After every change: run lint, typecheck, and tests (or at least build).

If you hit an error: fix it before adding any new features.

Prefer simple, boring implementations over clever ones.

Tailwind arbitrary values in @apply inside .css files are NOT generated by JIT.
Tailwind JIT only scans .tsx/.jsx files for class names. If a class like
sm:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_280px] appears only inside a .css @apply rule,
it will be silently ignored and the style will not render.
Rule: for any layout-critical CSS that uses arbitrary values or complex responsive
grid/flex rules, write raw CSS properties directly (with @media blocks) instead
of relying on @apply with arbitrary Tailwind classes.
